{"id":41219,"date":"2023-09-27T20:56:37","date_gmt":"2023-09-27T16:56:37","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=41219"},"modified":"2023-09-27T20:56:37","modified_gmt":"2023-09-27T16:56:37","slug":"bidah-footsteps-anbiya","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/09\/27\/bidah-footsteps-anbiya\/","title":{"rendered":"Umar on Bid\u2019ah: Warning against innovated worship"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Al-Ma\u2019mur ibn Suwayd reported: We were with Umar, may Allah be pleased with him, between Mecca and Medina, and we performed the dawn prayer. Then, he saw people descending to pray in a mosque. Umar asked about them, and they said, \u201cIt is a mosque in which the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, performed prayer.\u201d Umar said, \u201cVerily, those before you were destroyed for taking the footprints of their Prophets as a transaction! Whoever passes by any mosque while it is time to pray, let him pray there, or if not, let him move on.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Mus\u0323annaf &#8216;Abd al-Razza\u0304q 2734<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Arna\u2019ut<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0639\u0652\u0631\u064f\u0648\u0631\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0633\u064f\u0648\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062f\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064f\u0646\u0652\u062a\u064f \u0645\u064e\u0639\u064e \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064f \u0628\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0646\u064e \u0645\u064e\u0643\u064e\u0651\u0629\u064e \u0648\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064e\u062f\u0650\u064a\u0646\u064e\u0629\u0650 \u0641\u064e\u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0628\u0650\u0646\u064e\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0641\u064e\u062c\u0652\u0631\u064e \u062b\u064f\u0645\u064e\u06